history.content: You'll be fine, but expect a constant heavy workload throughout the semester.

children.subject: I did this Fall 2017 and it was a tough semester. 61C isn't like 61A/B where you have 1-2 topics to focus on per week. You get a lot thrown at you and you'll be expected to pick up on it quickly and implement the ideas in the projects (there are 4 or 5). 170 on the other hand, is similar in structure to 70, so you want to leave yourself sufficient time to work on the homework because that is where all the learning happens. Don't fall behind and you'll be good to go.

I am doing that rn and would not recommend that workload unless you really want to spend a lot of time on weekly psets for 170 and very time-consuming and heavy hws / projects for 61c (they are also usually weekly). I would recommend you to space them out, as they together really feels like 3 average technicals together

history.content: Doing this for the upcoming semester.  Any thoughts on this combo with an "easy" breadth?
